{"content": "<div id=\"problemtext\"><h2><a href=\"https://gpe3.acm-icpc.tw/domjudge2/pct/showproblem.php?probid=22161&amp;cid=5\" target=\"_blank\">22161:Euclid Problem</a></h2>Time Limit: 3 sec<p></p><h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Description</h3><p><span class=\"Apple\" style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium 'Times New Roman'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">From Euclid it is known that for any positive integers<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>A</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>B</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>there exist such integers&#160;<em>X</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>Y</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>that<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>AX+BY=D</em>, where<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>D</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>is the greatest common divisor of<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>A</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>B</em>. The problem is to find for given<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>A</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>B</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>corresponding<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>X</em>,<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>Y</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>D</em>.</span></p><h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Input</h3><p><span class=\"Apple\" style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium 'Times New Roman'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">The input will consist of a set of lines with the integer numbers<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>A</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>B</em>, separated with space (<em>A,B&lt;1000000001</em>).</span></p><h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Output</h3><p><span class=\"Apple\" style=\"word-spacing: 0px; font: medium 'Times New Roman'; text-transform: none; color: #000000; text-indent: 0px; white-space: normal; letter-spacing: normal; border-collapse: separate; orphans: 2; widows: 2;\">For each input line the output line should consist of three integers<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>X, Y</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>D,</em>separated with space. If there are several such<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>X</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>Y</em>, you should output that pair for which<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>|X|+|Y|</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>is the minimal (primarily) and<span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span><em>X&lt;=Y</em><span class=\"Apple\">&#160;</span>(secondarily).</span></p><hr /><div id=\"sampleinputoutput\"><table class=\"inputoutput\"><tr><td class=\"SampleCaption\"><h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Sample Input</h3></td><td class=\"SampleCaption\"><h3 style=\"text-align:left\">Sample Output</h3></td></tr><tr></tr><tr class=\"inputoutput\"><td class=\"inputoutput\" valign=\"top\"><pre class=\"sampleio\">4 6&#13;\n17 17</pre></td><td class=\"inputoutput\" valign=\"top\"><pre class=\"sampleio\">-1 1 2&#13;\n0 1 17</pre></td></tr></table></div><hr /><table><tr><td>Source: </td><td>http://uva.onlinejudge.org/external/101/10104.html</td></tr><tr><td>Keyword:</td><td></td></tr></table></div></body>\n</html><html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\"></html>"}